  ## Every(interval, action)

  Function to start a goroutine that repeatedly executes at a specific interval of time.

  - **interval** - interval to run action on
  - **action** - action to perform on interval

  Returns a value every interval of time.

  ### Examples:

      :::bash
      gobot.Every("0.5s", func() { fmt.Println("Greetings human") })

  ## After(interval, action)

  Function to start a goroutine that repeatedly executes after waiting a specified number of milliseconds.

